article.headline: W. Carolina 110, Tenn. Wesleyan 67
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Jake Robinson scored 19 points and was one of seven Western Carolina players to score in double figures for the Catamounts in a 110-67 rout of Tennessee-Wesleyan on Monday night. Greg Avery scored 14 points, Kendall Russell had 12 and Keaton Cole and Dominique Quarles each added 11 for the Catamounts (5-2). Adrian Gailliard and Brandon Giles scored 10 apiece. Blake Gallagher grabbed a game-high 11 rebounds. Robinson was also 5-for-7 from beyond the arc and 2-for-2 from the free-throw line. Reggie Jackson scored a game-high 29 points to lead the Bulldogs (5-6), and Willie Maclin added 10. Jackson was perfect on 3-pointers, going 7-for-7. He also hit 4 of 4 free throws. The Catamounts had 69 bench points compared to 21 for the Bulldogs.
